post_text: Due to the poor air quality in Orondo our food service delivery will again be canceled for tomorrow. We are using the state department of ecology for our guidelines. When the air quality is poorer than 200 by 4pm the day prior we will not be sending staff out on buses to deliver. Our apologies for the inconvenience this causes, but the health of our students and staff is paramount.

post_text: Today Washington state Governor Jay Inslee announced the closure of all schools statewide effective Tuesday morning March 17th, 2020 through April 24th. post_text:
NOTICE OF SPECIAL MEETING
INFORME DE JUNTA ESPECIAL
The Board of Directors of Orondo School District will hold a Special Meeting on December 10, 2019, at 7:00PM in the Orondo School District, 100 Orondo School Road, for the purpose of considering and acting upon the following:
1. Resolution No. 2019-03, which provides for the submission to the District’s voters, at a special election to be held on February 11, 2020, of a proposition authorizing the District to impose a two-year Renewal of Expiring Educational Programs and Operation Levy.

La Mesa Directiva del Distrito Escolar de Orondo tendrá una junta especial el 10 de diciembre de 2019 a las 7:00 PM en el Distrito Escolar de Orondo, 100 Orondo School Road, con el propósito de considerar y actuar sobre lo siguiente:

1. Resolución No. 2019-03, que provee la presentación a los votantes del Distrito, en una elección especial que se llevará a cabo el 11 de febrero de 2020, para una propuesta que autoriza al Distrito a imponer una Renovación de dos años de un Levy expirando de Programas Educativos y Operación.

SafeSchools Alert system is used for parents and or students to inform the school of any threats, bullying, intimidation, harassment, weapons, drugs, and anything else that would jeopardize safety students, staff, or school. All you have to do is either download the SafeSchool Alert app located in your app store or log on to the Orondo School Website and click on the link http://orondo.wa.safeschoolsalert.com located right above the picture carousel. Through that link is where you can anonymously report any issues that you may have for administration to then review and proceed with a solution.

post_text: November 28th, Speaker Roberto Dansie, PhD will be here at Orondo School to speak on the topic of: El poder interior de la resilencia y la esperanza. We will be hosting a potluck style dinner Orondo School will provide the main dish which will be Tacos, we ask anyone who is planning to attend that they bring a side dish or dessert to share. Dinner will start at 5:30pm with speaker to follow. We will also have daycare and a pizza dinner for ages 1yrs old to 11yrs, all other children must remain with parents during this time. Waterville and Chelan residents are also welcome to attend this presentation. Please RSVP to Vanessa Medina at 509-784-1333 ASAP

post_text: Just a reminder Missoula Children's Theater will be here next week starting Monday October 22. The schedule for he week will be as follows. Monday all student with a main part in in the play will stay from 3:00pm-5:00pm you will receive a messenger call/text. Tuesday thru Thursday 1st rehearsal session is from 2:15-4:15pm. 2nd session rehearsal is from 4:30pm to 6:30pm. All students staying for rehearsals after school will be provided a snack. Friday 9:30am-12:00pm will be dress rehearsal for entire cast. 12:30pm-1:30pm pre-show prep for entire cast. 1:30pm will be the performance for all school, parents are also welcome come and watch as well. Saturday will be the main performance. Entire cast must be at school by 11am and performance to follow at 1:30pm. Performance will be open to all community members.

post_text: Some of the students that attend the after school program grades 3-8 were given the chance to participate in a two day basketball camp held after school hours coached by Ms. Regan and Mrs. Rosiles. During the Camp the students learned the fundamentals of how to handle a basketball from dribbling to how to shoot a ball into the basketball hoop. Students also had a chance to play small group scrimmage's and dribbling games. We will be holding another basketball camp shortly after the Winter Break, this will be opened to students 3-8 grade that do not currently participate in the after school program. Dates are still to be determined!
